bus1 - Base System Tools

org.bus1.rdinit: /init to use in the initrd:
        - mouts /dev, /sys, /proc, /dev/pts, /sys/fs/bus1
        - reads the kernel commandline:
        - "disk=UUID" looks (and waits) for the disk with the given GPT UUID,
          on that disk, it looks for the first GPT partition with the GPT
          partition type UUID of e0243462-d2d0-4c3b-ad28-b365f2da3b4d
        - "partition=<partition device node>" specifies the partition to mount
        - starts org.bus1.devices
        - mounts the bus1 partition to /bus1
        - mounts the system squashfs image in /bus1/system/<release>.img to /usr
        - symlinks /bus1/data to /var
        - executes org.bus1.init

org.bus1.init: init process PID1
        - starts org.bus1.activator
        - starts tty login
        - starts serial console if console=<device> is given on the kernel
          command line

org.bus1.activator: system service activator
        - sets up the service environment:
                - a new mount namespace
                - a separate tmpfs /
                - mounts the kernel filesystems
                - mounts /usr with the system image
                - mounts /var with the /var/bus1/<service> data directory
        - starts org.bus1.devices

org.bus1.devices: hotplug device manager and kernel module loader
        - listens to kernel uevents
        - crawls /sys for coldplug
        - adjusts platform permissions in /dev
        - loads kernel modules for plugged devices

